uleta]] \u2013 '''2''' ([[2001\u201302 French Division 1|2001\u201302]], [[2002\u201303 Ligue 1|2002\u201303]] \u2013 {{flagicon|FRA}} [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]])\n*[[Cristiano Ronaldo]] \u2013 '''2''' ([[2006\u201307 Premier League|2006\u201307]], [[2007\u201308 Premier League|2007\u201308]] \u2013 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]])\n*[[S\u00e9rgio Concei\u00e7\u00e3o]] \u2013 '''1''' ([[2004\u201305 Belgian First Division|2004\u201305]] \u2013 {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]])\n*[[Hugo Vieira]] \u2013 '''1''' ([[2015\u201316 Serbian SuperLiga|2015\u201316]] \u2013 {{flagicon|SER}} [[Red Star Belgrade]])\n*[[Miguel V\u00edtor]] \u2013 '''1''' ([[2016\u201317 Israeli Premier League|2016\u201317]] \u2013 {{flagicon|ISR}} [[Hapoel Be'er Sheva F.C.|Hapoel Be'er Sheva]])\n\n;Domestic league top scorer\nThe following players have won a domestic league top scorer award while playing in foreign division teams:\n*[[Cristiano Ronaldo]] \u2013 '''4''' ([[2007\u201308 Premier League#Statistics|2007\u201308]] \u2013 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], [[2010\u201311 La Liga#Awards and season statistics|2010\u201311]], [[2013\u201314 La Liga#Awards and season statistics|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 La Liga#Awards and season statistics|2014\u201315]] \u2013 {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]])\n*[[Pauleta]] \u2013 '''4''' ([[1996\u201397 Segunda Divisi\u00f3n|1996\u201397]] \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[UD Salamanca|Salamanca]], [[2001\u201302 French Division 1#Top goalscorers|2001\u201302]] \u2013 {{flagicon|FRA}} [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]], [[2005\u201306 Ligue 1#Top goalscorers|2005\u201306]], [[2006\u201307 Ligue 1#Top goalscorers|2006\u201307]] \u2013 {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]])\n*[[Jorge Cadete]] \u2013 '''1''' ([[1996\u201397 Scottish Premier Division#Top scorers|1996\u201397]] \u2013 {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]])\n*[[Jos\u00e