 Real Madrid C.F. season|2014\u201315]]\n*Most goals for a single club in all competitions (top ten list):\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n!\n! Name\n! Years\n! League\n! Club\n! Goals\n|-\n|1||[[Cristiano Ronaldo]]||2009\u20132018||{{flagicon|Spain}} [[La Liga]]||[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]||align=center|'''450'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|2||[[Cristiano Ronaldo]]||2003\u20132009||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Premier League]]||[[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]||align=center|'''117'''\n|-\n|3||[[Pauleta]]||2003\u20132008||{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Ligue 1]]||[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]]||align=center|'''109'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|4||[[Pauleta]]||2000\u20132003||{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Ligue 1]]||[[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]]||align=center|'''91'''\n|-\n|5||[[Danny (footballer)|Danny]]||2009\u20132017||{{flagicon|Russia}} [[Russian Football Premier League|Russian Premier League]]||[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit]]||align=center|'''68'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|6||[[Hugo Almeida]]||2006\u20132010||{{flagicon|GER}} [[Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|Bundesliga]]||[[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]||align=center|'''63'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|-\n|7||[[Lu\u00eds Figo]]||2000\u20132005||{{flagicon|Spain}} [[La Liga]]||[[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]||align=center|'''57'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|8||[[Paulo Futre]]||1987\u20131993||{{flagicon|Spain}} [[La Liga]]||[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]||align=center|'''51'''\n|-\n|9||[[Rui Costa]]||1994\u20132001||{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Serie A]]||[[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]||align=center|'''50'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|10||[[Lu\u00eds Figo]]||1995\u20132000||{{flagicon|Spain}} [[La Liga]]||[[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]||align=center|'''47'''\n|}\n\n==Appearances==\n{{Updated|22 January 2019}}\n\n===Domestic league===\n:''Top division of the respective country only.''\n*Most appearances in a domestic league: \n**'''339''' \u2013 [[Rui Costa]], {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Serie A]] ([[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] and [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]), 1994\u20132006\n*Most appearances in a domestic league for a single club: \n**'''292''' \u2013 [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], {{flagicon|ESP}} [[La Liga]] ([[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]), 2009\u20132018\n\n===All competitions===\n:''Players who have spent all seasons in the top division of the respective country.''\n*Most appearances in a season in all competitions:\n**'''60''' - [[Bernardo Silva]], {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester City FC|Manchester City]], [[2018\u201319 Manchester City FC season|2018\u201319]]\n*Most appearances for a single club in all competitions (top ten list):\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n!\n! Name\n! Years\n! Club\n! League\n! Apps\n|-\n|1||[[Cristiano Ronaldo|Ronaldo]]||2009\u20132018 ||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]||[[La Liga]]||align=center|'''438'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|2||[[Duda (Portuguese footballer)|Duda]]||2001\u20132006, 2008\u20132017||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]||[[La Liga]]||align=center|'''348'''\n|-\n|3||[[Pepe (footballer, born 1983)|Pepe]]||2007\u20132017 ||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]||[[La Liga]]||align=center|'''334'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|4||[[Cristiano Ronaldo|Ronaldo]]||2003\u20132009||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]||[[Premier League]]||align=center|'''289'''\n|-\n|5||[[Rui Costa]]||1994\u20132001||{{flagicon|ITA}} [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]||[[Serie A]]||align=center|'''276'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|6||'''[[Anthony Lopes]]'''||2012-''present''||{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]]||[[Ligue 1]]||align=center|'''264'''\n|-\n|7||[[Lu\u00eds Figo]]||1995\u20132000||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]||[[La Liga]]||align=center|'''249'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|8||[[Danny (footballer)|Danny]]||2008\u20132017||{{flagicon|RUS}} [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit]]||[[Russian Premier League]]||align=center|'''246'''\n|-\n|9||[[Lu\u00eds Figo]]||2000\u20132005||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]||[[La Liga]]||align=center|'''239'''\n|-style=\"background:#EEEEFF\"\n|10||[[Nani]]||2007\u20132015||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]||[[Premier League]]||align=center|'''230'''\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n=== Team honours ===\n*Most domestic league titles: '''8''' \u2013 [[Lu\u00eds Figo]] (2 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], 2 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], 4 \u2013 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]])\n*Most domestic league titles for a single club: '''4''' \u2013 [[Lu\u00eds Figo]] ({{flagicon|ITA}} [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]])\n*Most domestic cup titles: '''5''' \u2013 [[Manuel Fernandes (footballer, born 1986)|Manuel Fernandes]] (1 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], 1 \u2013 {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]], 3 \u2013 {{flagicon|RUS}} [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]])\n*Most [[UEFA Champions League]] titles: '''5''' \u2013 [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] (1 \u2013 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United]], 4 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]])\n*Most [[UEFA Cup Winner's Cup]] titles: '''2''' \u2013 [[Fernando Couto]] (1 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], 1 \u2013 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]])\n*Most [[UEFA Europa League]] titles: '''3'''\n** [[Daniel Carri\u00e7o]] (3 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]])\n** [[Diogo Figueiras]] (3 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]])\n*Most [[UEFA competitions]] titles: '''7''' \u2013 [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] (1 \u2013 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Manchester United]], 6 \u2013 {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]])\n*Most titles with a club: '''15''' \n**[[Cristiano Ronaldo]] ({{flagicon|ESP}} [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]])\n*Most titles overall: '''24'''\n**[[Cristiano Ronaldo]] (9 \u20