340</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-4560023&fid=5791&c=somalia Dararweyne]\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Sanaag]]\n\n{{Somaliland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ducaysane911", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dararweyne"}
{"title_page": "Garadag", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Garadag\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = District\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = Somaliland\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Somaliland.\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Somaliland}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Administrative divisions of Somaliland|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sanaag]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Administrative divisions of Somaliland|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[town]]\n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Imperial\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 17,400\n| population_density_km2          = \n| timezone                        = [[East Africa Time|EAT]]\n| utc_offset                      = +3\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|9|29|15|N|46|52|1|E|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n}}\n\n'''Garadag''' ({{lang-so|Gar Adag}}) is  a [[small town in Somaliland  of the northern [[Sanaag]] region of [[Somaliland]].<ref>https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=CKQ7AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA223&lpg=PA223&dq=garadag+somalia&source=bl&ots=q6miyK1L4k&sig=ACfU3U0wTz8u1fKKQ8wlB6C3SaLeoCaIrA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwis7OLT27PnAhUkRhUIHVvcBQs4ChDoATAJegQIChAB#v=onepage&q=garadag%20somalia&f=false</ref>\nThe city is inhabited by people from the [[Habr Je'lo|Habar Jeclo]] sub-tribe of the [[Isaaq]]. \n\n==Overview==\nGaradag is located northwest of [[Xudun, Somalia|Xudun]] and east by road from [[War Idaad]].{{fact|date=December 2019}} The town is primarily inhabited by people from the Somali ethnic group, with the [[Habar Jeclo]] sub-clan of [[Isaaq]] well-represented.\n\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Somaliland}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://garadag.org/drupal/ Official site]\n*[http://www.maplandia.com/somalia/sanaag/ceel-afwein/garadag/ Maplandia World Gazetteer]\n*[http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-4563997&fid=5790&c=somalia Garadag]\n\n[[Category:Somaliland]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Sanaag]]\n[[Category:Sanaag]]\n\n\n{{Somalia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Garadag\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = \n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = District\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = Somaliland\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Somaliland.\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Somaliland}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Administrative divisions of Somaliland|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sanaag]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Administrative divisions of Somaliland|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[District]]\n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Imperial\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 17,400\n| population_density_km2          = \n| timezone                        = [[East Africa Time|EAT]]\n| utc_offset                      = +3\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|9|29|15|N|46|52|1|E|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n}}\n\n'''Garadag''' ({{lang-so|Gar Adag}}) is  a [[Administrative divisions of Somaliland|District]] of the northern [[Sanaag]] region of [[Somaliland]].<ref>https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=CKQ7AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA223&lpg=PA223&dq=garadag+somalia&source=bl&ots=q6miyK1L4k&sig=ACfU3U0wTz8u1fKKQ8wlB6C3SaLeoCaIrA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwis7OLT27PnAhUkRhUIHVvcBQs4ChDoATAJegQIChAB#v=onepage&q=garadag%20somalia&f=false</ref>\nThe city is inhabited by people from the [[Habr Je'lo|Habar Jeclo]] sub-tribe of the [[Isaaq]]. \n\n==Overview==\nGaradag is located northwest of [[Xudun, Somalia|Xudun]] and east by road from [[War Idaad]].{{fact|date=December 2019}} The town is primarily inhabited by people from the Somali ethnic group, with the [[Habar Jeclo]] sub-clan of [[Isaaq]] well-represented.\n\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Somaliland}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://garadag.org/drupal/ Official site]\n*[http://www.maplandia.com/somalia/sanaag/ceel-afwein/garadag/ Maplandia World Gazetteer]\n*[http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-4563997&fid=5790&c=somalia Garadag]\n\n[[Category:Somaliland]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Sanaag]]\n[[Category:Sanaag]]\n\n\n{{Somalia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ducaysane911", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garadag"}
{"title_page": "Heis (town)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Heis\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = Xiis\n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = Town\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = Somaliland\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Somaliland.\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Somaliland}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Administrative divisions of Somalia|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sanaag]]\n| subdivision_type2               = \n| subdivision_name2               = \n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = \n| population_density_km2          = \n| timezone                        = [[East Africa Time|EAT]]\n| utc_offset                      = +3\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|10|53|47|N|46|55|16|E|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n}}\n\n'''Heis''' ({{lang-so|Xiis}}) is a historic coastal small town located in the [[Sanaag]] region of [[Somaliland]].<ref>https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10437-015-9184-9</ref>.<ref>https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.14321/nortafristud.18.1-2.0271?seq=1</ref> The settlement is inhabited by the [[Habr Je'lo]] sub-clan of the Isaaq.<ref>The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, Volume 19, p. 63, 1848</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe site said to be identical with the ancient trading post of '''Mundus''' (\u039c\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 in [[Ancient Greek]]) that is described in the ''[[Periplus of the Erythraean Sea]]'', an anonymous account by an [[Alexandria]]n salesman from the 1st century CE.<ref name=\"Periplus1\">[http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/ancient/periplus.html Periplus of the Erythraean Sea]</ref><ref name=\"Periplus2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ioz.unibe.ch/lenya/iop/live/periplus/mundu.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20070815093955/http://www.ioz.unibe.ch/lenya/iop/live/periplus/mundu.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2007-08-15 |title=Mundu |language=German |publisher=[[University of Bern]] }}</ref>\n\nA large collection of [[cairn]]s of various types lie near the city.<ref name=\"Nsaaaie\">{{cite book|title=Newsletter of the Society of Africanist Archaeologists in America, Issues 8-13|date=1976|publisher=Department of Archaeology, University of Calgary|page=5|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=KLEbAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> Excavations here have yielded pottery and sherds of [[Roman Empire|Roman]] glassware from a time between the 1st and 5th centuries.<ref name=\"Periplus1\"/><ref name=\"Periplus2\"/> Among these artefacts is high-quality [[millefiori]] glass.<ref name=\"Nsaaaie\"/> Dated to 0-40 CE, it features red flower disks superimposed on a green background.<ref name=\"Meyer\">{{cite book|last1=Meyer|first1=Carol|title=Glass from Quseir Al-Qadim and the Indian Ocean Trade, Issue 53|date=1992|publisher=Oriental Institute of the University of Chicago|isbn=0918986877|page=37|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=Hz5tAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> Additionally, an ancient fragment of a footed bowl was discovered in the surrounding area. The sherd is believed to have been made in [[Aswan]] (300-500 CE) or [[Lower Nubia]] (500-600 CE), suggesting early trading ties with kingdoms in the [[Nile Valley]].<ref name=\"Hatke152\">{{cite book|last1=Hatke|first1=George|title=Aksum and Nubia: Warfare, Commerce, and Political Fictions in Ancient Northeast Africa|date=2013|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=0814762832|page=152|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=Oy7N_d6HoYIC|accessdate=16 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-4576771&fid=5792&c=somalia Xiis, Somalia]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140221184840/http://www.storm247.com/weather/14616650/map Weather forecast for Heis , Somalia]\n[[Category:Archaeological sites in Somalia]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Sanaag]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek geography-East Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Heis\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = Xiis\n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = Town\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| pushpin_map                     = Somaliland\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Somaliland.\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Somaliland}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Administrative divisions of Somalia|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sanaag]]\n| subdivision_type2               = \n| subdivision_name2               = \n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = \n| population_density_km2          = \n| timezone                        = [[East Africa Time|EAT]]\n| utc_offset                      = +3\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|10|53|47|N|46|55|16|E|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n}}\n\n'''Heis''' ({{lang-so|Xiis}}) is a historic coastal town located in the [[Sanaag]] region of [[Somaliland]].<ref>https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10437-015-9184-9</ref>.<ref>https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.14321/nortafristud.18.1-2.0271?seq=1</ref> The settlement is inhabited by the [[Habr Je'lo]] sub-clan of the Isaaq.<ref>The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, Volume 19, p. 63, 1848</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe site said to be identical with the ancient trading post of '''Mundus''' (\u039c\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 in [[Ancient Greek]]) that is described in the ''[[Periplus of the Erythraean Sea]]'', an anonymous account by an [[Alexandria]]n salesman from the 1st century CE.<ref name=\"Periplus1\">[http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/ancient/periplus.html Periplus of the Erythraean Sea]</ref><ref name=\"Periplus2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ioz.unibe.ch/lenya/iop/live/periplus/mundu.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20070815093955/http://www.ioz.unibe.ch/lenya/iop/live/periplus/mundu.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2007-08-15 |title=Mundu |language=German |publisher=[[University of Bern]] }}</ref>\n\nA large collection of [[cairn]]s of various types lie near the city.<ref name=\"Nsaaaie\">{{cite book|title=Newsletter of the Society of Africanist Archaeologists in America, Issues 8-13|date=1976|publisher=Department of Archaeology, University of Calgary|page=5|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=KLEbAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> Excavations here have yielded pottery and sherds of [[Roman Empire|Roman]] glassware from a time between the 1st and 5th centuries.<ref name=\"Periplus1\"/><ref name=\"Periplus2\"/> Among these artefacts is high-quality [[millefiori]] glass.<ref name=\"Nsaaaie\"/> Dated to 0-40 CE, it features red flower disks superimposed on a green background.<ref name=\"Meyer\">{{cite book|last1=Meyer|first1=Carol|title=Glass from Quseir Al-Qadim and the Indian Ocean Trade, Issue 53|date=1992|publisher=Oriental Institute of the University of Chicago|isbn=0918986877|page=37|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=Hz5tAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> Additionally, an ancient fragment of a footed bowl was discovered in the surrounding area. The sherd is believed to have been made in [[Aswan]] (300-500 CE) or [[Lower Nubia]] (500-600 CE), suggesting early trading ties with kingdoms in the [[Nile Valley]].<ref name=\"Hatke152\">{{cite book|last1=Hatke|first1=George|title=Aksum and Nubia: Warfare, Commerce, and Political Fictions in Ancient Northeast Africa|date=2013|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=0814762832|page=152|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=Oy7N_d6HoYIC|accessdate=16 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-4576771&fid=5792&c=somalia Xiis, Somalia]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140221184840/http://www.storm247.com/weather/14616650/map Weather forecast for Heis , Somalia]\n[[Category:Archaeological sites in Somalia]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Sanaag]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek geography-East Africa]]\n", "name_user": "Ducaysane911", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heis_(town)"}
